   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help Rebuild Former Refugees&apos; Lives in Afghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Facing a fragile peace and a society torn apart by war, the UN Refugee Agency (UNHCR) has much still to do in Afghanistan. Since 2002, UNHCR&apos;s voluntary repatriation program has assisted more than 4.6 million Afghan refugees to return home. But, the journey home is just the beginning. Providing shelter is part of the UN Refugee Agency&apos;s core mandate and vital to ensuring that returns are sustainable.  Since 2002, UNHCR has helped over 205,000 families rebuild their homes.</narrative>
  </description>
